sentences: Miho Katō (加藤 美穂, Katō Miho) (born June 22, 1988), better known by her stage name of Miliyah Kato (加藤 ミリヤ, Katō Miriya) is a Japanese pop and urban singer, songwriter, fashion designer, and author.
In 2003, Kato started her career as a singer when she provided vocal to Reggae Disco Rockers' song "Cherry
Her hip-hop-influenced debut album, Rose (2005) was certified platinum in Japan.
She gained further recognition when she was featured in M-Flo's track "One Day" (2005).
She gained further recognition when she was featured in M-Flo's track "One Day" (2005).
Her third studio album, Tokyo Star (2008) yielded her first top-ten single, "La La La", which was later certified double-platinum for its ringtone sales.
Kato's first compilation album Best Destiny (2008) became her first number-one album, certified platinum in Japan.
Her fifth studio album Heaven (2010) debuted atop on the Oricon chart and has yielded two platinum singles, "Why" and "Last Love".
Kato's second compilation album M Best (2011) became her second consecutive number one album, selling over 300,000 copies nationwide.
In 2011, Kato published her first novel, "Umareta mama no Watashi wo", which marked her debut as an author.
Her sixth and seventh studio album True Lovers (2012) and Loveland (2014) reached top three in Japan.

In 2014, Kato recorded a collaborative album, The Best, with a Japanese singer-songwriter Shota Shimizu.

Her tenth studio album, Femme Fatale (2018) was released to a minor commercial success, only reaching number eight in Japan.
Regarded as one of the biggest J-pop musicians in the late 2000s and the early 2010s, Kato has sold over 12.6 million records and ringtones.
